<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="318" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d318">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 181.9202/169:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Bandholtz</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate
                            Peace</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-04">October 4, 1919</date>.<lb/>[Received October
                                4—6:30 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>118. As a necessary step to prevent some of the suffering that is sure to
                            ensue from food and fuel shortage it is recommended that the Roumanians
                            be obliged to return immediately such portions of seized Hungary rolling
                            stock as directed by Interallied Military Mission.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bandholtz</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>